comments: MOB shows Noah (MEM) establishes a wide screening position in Sexton's (CLE) path and contact occurs to his leg/foot.
Noah (MEM) makes some contact with Nance Jr. (CLE) during the rebound but the contact does not affect his ability to retrieve the ball.
Bradley (MEM) places a hand/arm to the front of Osman (CLE) during the drive but the contact does not affect his SQBR.
Conely (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in Nance Jr.'s (CLE) path and makes some contact with his backside but he is able to move through contact.
Valanciunas (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Dellavedova (CLE) and does not deliver contact.
Valanciunas (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Dellavedova (CLE) and absorbs the contact.
Zizic (CLE) makes some contact with Valanciunas (MEM) during the rebound but it does not affect his ability to retrieve the ball.
Zizic (CLE) slightly extends his arms against Conley (MEM) during the pick but he is able to move through contact.
Holiday (MEM) makes incidental contact to the arm of Osman (CLE) after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Conley (MEM) makes some contact with Nance Jr.'s (CLE) arm during the rebound but does not affect his ability to gather the ball.
Noah (MEM) makes some contact with Dellavedova's (CLE) side during the pick but he is able to move through contact.
Zizic (CLE) delivers contact to Valanciunas (MEM) during his shooting motion that affects his play at the basket.
Noah (MEM) briefly grasps Zizic's (CLE) arm during the rebound but it does not affect his ability to retrieve the ball.
Bradley (MEM) maintains legal guarding position as Osman (CLE) attempts to screen.
RAR shows Bradley (MEM) makes  contact to the body of Dellavedova (CLE) during his shooting motion that does not affect his driving shot attempt.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of defensive goaltending was overturned (this was called but it is entered as a correct non-call so that it can be included in the last two minute report).
RAR shows Valanciunas (MEM) establishes a screening position in Delladova's (CLE) path and makes some leg contact during the screen but he is able to move through contact.

LAR shows Sexton (CLE) secures the rebound and falls to the floor. When in possession of the ball while on the floor, an offensive player is permitted to stand up, establish a pivot foot and resume play.
LAR shows Zizic (CLE) clamps the arm of Valanciunas (MEM) and affects his ability to elevate for the loose ball during the rebound.
Valanciunas (MEM) commits a take foul on Sexton (CLE).
Conley (MEM) briefly grasps Dellavedova's (CLE) arm but does not affect his FOM.
Wright (MEM) commits a take foul on Dellavedova (CLE).
Dellavedova (CLE) engages with Conley (MEM) but does not affect his FOM.
Nance Jr. (CLE) makes marginal contact to the body of Noah (MEM) during the putback attempt that does not affect his play at the basket.
Nance Jr. (CLE) makes some contact with Noah (MEM) during the rebound but does not affect his ability to retrieve the ball.
Valanciunas (MEM) commits a take foul on Nance Jr. (CLE).
Valanciunas (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Dellavedova (CLE) and gives him room to avoid contact.
Holiday (MEM) commits a take foul on Dellavedova (CLE).
